    slug: "islam-a-total-beginners-guide-1",
    description: `Islam: A Total Beginner's Guide (Part 1) is the first volume in a comprehensive English-language series designed to introduce the complete fundamentals of Islam to readers who have little or no prior knowledge of the religion. Written in clear, accessible, and non-technical language, this book is specifically designed for new Muslims who have recently embraced Islam and need a structured introduction to the beliefs and practices of their new faith, for non-Muslims who are curious about Islam and want an accurate and unbiased overview, and for anyone who wants to refresh their understanding of the basic teachings of Islam. The first volume lays the essential groundwork by covering the most fundamental concepts that form the foundation of the entire Islamic belief system and practice.

The book opens with an introduction to the concept of Islam itself, explaining the linguistic meaning of the word "Islam" (submission to the will of Allah) and the significance of this definition as the defining characteristic of the Muslim identity. It then proceeds to cover the six articles of faith (arkan al-iman) in detail: belief in Allah as the one and only God, belief in the angels (mala'ikah) as created beings who carry out Allah's commands, belief in the revealed books (kutub) including the Torah, the Psalms, the Gospel, and the Quran, belief in the prophets and messengers (rusul) from Adam to Muhammad (peace be upon them all), belief in the Day of Judgment (yawm al-qiyamah) and the accountability of human deeds, and belief in divine decree (qadar) — the Islamic understanding of predestination and human free will. Each article of faith is explained with reference to the relevant Quranic verses and hadith narrations, and common misconceptions about each article are addressed with clarity and sensitivity.

The book then introduces the five pillars of Islam (arkan al-Islam): the declaration of faith (shahadah), the five daily prayers (salah), the obligatory charity (zakat), fasting during the month of Ramadan (sawm), and the pilgrimage to Makkah (hajj). For each pillar, the book provides a practical, step-by-step explanation of how it is performed, the wisdom and purpose behind it, and the specific rulings that govern its observance. The section on salah includes detailed instructions on how to perform ablution (wudu) and the prayer itself, with clear descriptions of the physical postures and the recitations involved. The English prose is warm and welcoming in tone, acknowledging that the process of learning about Islam can be overwhelming for beginners and presenting the information in manageable, well-organized sections that build upon each other logically. This book is an ideal starting point for anyone beginning their journey into Islam, whether as a new Muslim, a curious seeker, or a lifelong learner.`,
    metaDescription: "Islam A Total Beginners Guide Part 1 is an English introduction to Islamic faith. Covers six articles of faith, five pillars, prayer, and basic beliefs."
