    slug: "islam-a-total-beginners-guide-3-vols",
    description: `Islam: A Total Beginner's Guide (3 Volumes Set) is a complete three-volume English-language course that provides a comprehensive and progressive introduction to Islam, taking the reader from the most basic concepts of Islamic belief and practice to more advanced topics of Islamic law, ethics, history, and spirituality. The three-volume set is designed as a complete self-study curriculum for new Muslims, non-Muslims interested in understanding Islam, Islamic school students, and anyone who wants a thorough and well-organized reference guide to the teachings of Islam presented in clear, accessible English. By packaging all three volumes together, this set provides a complete learning pathway that can be followed systematically from start to finish or used as a reference by readers who want to look up specific topics.

The first volume covers the foundational beliefs and practices of Islam, including a detailed explanation of the six articles of faith — belief in Allah, the angels, the revealed books, the prophets, the Day of Judgment, and divine decree — and the five pillars of Islam — the declaration of faith, prayer, charity, fasting, and pilgrimage. Each topic is explained with reference to the Quran and hadith, and the practical aspects of each pillar are described in step-by-step detail so that the reader knows exactly how to perform the essential acts of worship. The first volume also covers the basic moral and ethical principles of Islam, the concept of halal and haram, and the Islamic perspective on the purpose of human existence.

The second volume builds upon this foundation by introducing more detailed aspects of Islamic knowledge, including the biography of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), the history of Islam from its beginning to the present day, the lives of the major companions and scholars, and the development of the various Islamic sciences including Quranic exegesis (tafsir), hadith studies, Islamic jurisprudence (fiqh), and Islamic theology (aqeedah). The second volume also covers the Islamic perspective on contemporary social issues, including family life, marriage, divorce, parenting, business ethics, and the rights and responsibilities of individuals within the Muslim community.

The third volume addresses more advanced and specialized topics, including a detailed study of the Quran as a literary and miraculous text, the methodology of Islamic jurisprudence (usul al-fiqh), the history of the different schools of Islamic law, the principles of Islamic spirituality and self-purification (tazkiyah), the major theological debates in Islamic history, and a comparative study of Islam with other major world religions. The third volume also includes guidance on the Islamic approach to seeking knowledge, the etiquette of the student of knowledge, and recommendations for further reading and study. Throughout all three volumes, the English prose maintains its clarity and accessibility, and the material is presented in a way that respects the intelligence of the reader while not assuming any prior knowledge of Islam. The three-volume set comes in a durable binding suitable for long-term use and reference, making it a valuable addition to any home or institutional library.`,
